  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "The combination of exact version numbers/OS in the current Client ID string can be used to help fingerprint a particular node. To enhance privacy, it would be nice to be able to modify this string, and preferably have it default to something more generic in a future update.\r\n\r\nFor example: Nethermind/v1.19.0+19d3be4a/linux-x64/dotnet7.0.5\r\n\r\nIt would be nice to have this string configurable via the config file, and to have the default be something generic like \"Nethermind/eth-client\". Maybe the config option could accept an array of possible ClientIDs, and randomly choose one from the array on each restart. ",
